### member-management.http
###
### Member Management API scenarios
### Tests for creating, reading, updating members
###
### Usage: Use with IntelliJ HTTP Client or similar tools
### Requires: Variable `apiBaseUrl` defined in http-client.env.json
###

### Test 1: Create minimal member (required fields only)
POST {{apiBaseUrl}}/members
Authorization: Bearer {{$auth.token("AuthorizationCode")}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Tomas",
  "lastName": "Cerny",
  "gender": "MALE",
  "nationality": "CZ",
  "dateOfBirth": "1992-03-10",
  "address": {
    "street": "Test 1",
    "city": "Ostrava",
    "postalCode": "70000",
    "country": "CZ"
  },
  "email": "tomas.cerny@example.com",
  "phone": "+420603111222"
}

> {%
    client.global.set('memberId', response.body.id)
%}

###

### Test 2: Create member with optional fields (birthPlace and notes)
POST {{apiBaseUrl}}/members
Authorization: Bearer {{$auth.token("AuthorizationCode")}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Petra",
  "lastName": "Dvorakova",
  "gender": "FEMALE",
  "nationality": "CZ",
  "dateOfBirth": "1988-12-05",
  "birthPlace": "Brno",
  "address": {
    "street": "Hlavna 1",
    "city": "Brno",
    "postalCode": "60000",
    "country": "CZ"
  },
  "contact": {
    "email": "petra.dvorakova@example.com",
    "phone": "+420604333444"
  },
  "notes": "Former member, rejoining the club"
}

###

### Test 3: Create member with national ID number (rodné číslo)
### Note: This field is encrypted in the database
POST {{apiBaseUrl}}/members
Authorization: Bearer {{$auth.token("AuthorizationCode")}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Lukas",
  "lastName": "Krejci",
  "gender": "MALE",
  "nationality": "CZ",
  "dateOfBirth": "1995-07-25",
  "nationalIdNumber": "9507251234",
  "address": {
    "street": "Mala 5",
    "city": "Olomouc",
    "postalCode": "77000",
    "country": "CZ"
  },
  "contact": {
    "email": "lukas.krejci@example.com",
    "phone": "+420605555666"
  }
}

###

### Test 4: Create member with all optional fields
POST {{apiBaseUrl}}/members
Authorization: Bearer {{$auth.token("AuthorizationCode")}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Eva",
  "lastName": "Horakova",
  "gender": "FEMALE",
  "nationality": "CZ",
  "dateOfBirth": "1991-09-18",
  "birthPlace": "Plzen",
  "nationalIdNumber": "9109185678",
  "address": {
    "street": "Riegrova 42",
    "city": "Plzen",
    "postalCode": "30100",
    "country": "CZ"
  },
  "contact": {
    "email": "eva.horakova@example.com",
    "phone": "+420606777888"
  },
  "notes": "Experienced orienteer, interested in coaching"
}

###

### Test 5: Validation error - missing required fields (address and contact)
POST {{apiBaseUrl}}/members
Authorization: Bearer {{$auth.token("AuthorizationCode")}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Invalid",
  "lastName": "Member",
  "gender": "MALE",
  "nationality": "CZ",
  "dateOfBirth": "1990-01-01"
}

### Expected: 400 Bad Request - missing address and contact

###

### Test 6: List members with pagination
GET {{apiBaseUrl}}/members?page=0&size=5&sort=lastName,asc
Authorization: Bearer {{$auth.token("AuthorizationCode")}}
Accept: application/prs.hal-forms+json

###

### Test 7: List members with different sort order
GET {{apiBaseUrl}}/members?page=0&size=10&sort=registrationNumber,desc
Authorization: Bearer {{$auth.token("AuthorizationCode")}}
Accept: application/prs.hal-forms+json

###

### Test 8: Get specific member by UUID
GET {{apiBaseUrl}}/members/{{memberId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{$auth.token("AuthorizationCode")}}
Accept: application/prs.hal-forms+json

### Note: Replace UUID with actual member ID from your database

###

### Test 9: Get non-existent member (404 error test)
GET {{apiBaseUrl}}/members/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Authorization: Bearer {{$auth.token("AuthorizationCode")}}
Accept: application/prs.hal-forms+json

### Expected: 404 Not Found

###

### Test 10: Update member (partial update)
PATCH {{apiBaseUrl}}/members/{{memberId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{$auth.token("AuthorizationCodeMember")}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "notes": "Updated notes - active member since 2024"
}

### Note: Replace UUID with actual member ID from your database

###

### Test 11: Update member with multiple fields
PATCH {{apiBaseUrl}}/members/{{memberId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{$auth.token("AuthorizationCodeMember")}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Jan Pavel",
  "birthPlace": "Praha",
  "notes": "Updated with additional information"
}

### Note: Replace UUID with actual member ID from your database

###

### Test 12: Update member - invalid UUID format
PATCH {{apiBaseUrl}}/members/invalid-uuid-format
Authorization: Bearer {{$auth.token("AuthorizationCode")}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "notes": "This should fail with invalid UUID"
}

### Expected: 400 Bad Request - invalid UUID format

###
